cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper deals with defending deep neural networks against adversarial examples, which is a common problem in computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) research. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes an end-to-end image compression model, which involves optimizing the trade-off between image quality and compression rate, indicating a potential connection to cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed method against various types of attacks, which falls under the scope of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
